# CinemaHunt

CinemaHunt is a movie database application that allows users to search for movies, view details, and save their favorite titles.
This project was built to demonstrate proficiency in API intergration, asynchronous JavaScript, and dynamic DOM manipulation.

## 🚀 Live Demo
https://github.com/Markis070/CinemaHunt.git

## 🛠️ Tech Stack
- **HTML5**: Structural layout.
- **CSS3**: Responsive design and styling.
- **JavaScript (ES6+)**: Logic, DOM manipulation, and API fetching.
- **OMDb API**: Intergration for dynamic movie data.

## ⚙️ Features
- **Real-time Search**: Search for any movie and get instant results.
- **Interactive Details**: View movie posters, release dates, and plot summaries.
- **Favorites System**: Users can save/remove movies from a local storage-backed favorites list.

## 📦 How to Run Locally
1. Clone this repository: `git clone https://github.com/Markis070/CinemaHunt.git`
2. Open `index.html` in your web browser.
3. (Recommended) Use the **Live Server** extension in VS Code to see changes in real-time.
